{
  "texts": [
    "Beliakov et al. (2020) express the learning problem as a difference of convex functions, making it amenable to DC (difference of convex) optimization methods and (local) linear programming.",
    "An approach based on linear programming is also proposed by Abbaszadeh and Hüllermeier (2021).",
    "An optimization technique based on the marginal contribution representation is explored by Beliakov and Divakov (2020).",
    "Thanks to this representation, the number of variables can be reduced, and the constraints can be simplified.",
    "• Another important class of MCDA models-outranking instead of utility-basedis the ELECTRE family."
  ]
}